    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-25T04:34:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-25T04:34:00-05:00" n="588"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d588">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/1164: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_SJF1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-25T18:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 25, 1919, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 25, 4:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your cable October 22, 6 p.m. Have no anxiety, there will [be] no abandonment the
                    work of Service Corps unless the Bolshevik runs some of them out.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
